      • getDataKey

        default java.lang.String getDataKey()
        The data key is used to uniquely identify the data within the node. It is used when comparing two tree node hierarchies to identify which nodes in one tree correspond to which nodes in the other. The tree view and row tree UI widgets use it to preserve the expansion state of a tree when the widget's value is refreshed with a new tree node that contains similar data to the previous one but may not have the same nodes expanded.

        The default implementation uses:

        • data.PublicID plus the data object's entity type name if the data is any persistent entity
        • data.toString() if the data object is any other non null object
        • "null" if the data object is null
        Implementors of this interface should override this method if the default implementation is not suitable, otherwise expansion state may not be preserved if the tree is used in a tree view or row tree.
